<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.files.downloads.read-write</key>
  <true/>
  <!--
    WALLET PERSISTENCE — keychain-access-groups.

    tenzro-device-key needs this entitlement to persist the Secure Enclave
    wallet key across restarts. Without it, SecKey::new(persistent) returns
    errSecMissingEntitlement (-34018) and the app falls back to a session-only
    key (wallet recreated each launch — graceful, by design).

    It is COMMENTED OUT because enabling it on a Developer-ID + hardened-runtime
    build with NO embedded provisioning profile makes macOS/AMFI SIGKILL the app
    at launch (<2s, no log output) — tested 2026-06-22. Even the app's OWN
    App-ID group requires a profile on macOS.

    TO ENABLE (one step once the profile is in place):
      1. Drop a current macOS `.provisionprofile` for App ID com.tenzro.studio
         (with the Keychain Sharing capability) at src-tauri/embedded.provisionprofile.
      2. Uncomment the `provisioningProfile` key in tauri.conf.json (macOS bundle).
      3. Uncomment the <key>/<array> block below.
      4. Rebuild + sign. The SE key lands in the default app keychain group
         R5FXGKNFBP.com.tenzro.studio (device_key uses DataProtectionKeychain,
         no explicit kSecAttrAccessGroup), so this single group is sufficient.

    The group string is $(AppIdentifierPrefix)<bundle-id> = team prefix + id.
  -->
  <!--
  <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
  <array>
    <string>R5FXGKNFBP.com.tenzro.studio</string>
  </array>
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
